00:06:49.920 --> 00:06:53.480
As your characters
point out in The Force,

00:06:53.480 --> 00:06:59.130
cops don't like to bare their souls
to anybody who's not in the club.

00:06:59.130 --> 00:07:00.430
&gt;&gt; Don Winslow: Yeah.

00:07:00.430 --> 00:07:01.730
&gt;&gt; Maureen Corrigan:
So was it the P.I.

00:07:01.730 --> 00:07:03.030
credentials that --

00:07:03.030 --> 00:07:04.330
&gt;&gt; Don Winslow: No, not at all.

00:07:04.330 --> 00:07:05.630
Typically cops don't like P.I.'s.

00:07:05.630 --> 00:07:09.210 position:56%
So that was not an advantage at all.

00:07:09.210 --> 00:07:15.870
No, it was -- I can't tell you how
many times I heard only other cops

00:07:15.870 --> 00:07:17.630
can understand me.

00:07:17.630 --> 00:07:19.170
Why don't we talk to other cops?

00:07:19.170 --> 00:07:21.900
And I think that that's a
real factor, and I get it.

00:07:21.900 --> 00:07:23.520
I understand why.

00:07:23.520 --> 00:07:25.840
Again, it was a matter of patience.

00:07:25.840 --> 00:07:28.110
And it was a matter
of, I think, empathy.

00:07:28.110 --> 00:07:31.710
I rarely go in and
ask what did you do?

00:07:31.710 --> 00:07:33.010
What happened?

00:07:33.010 --> 00:07:34.930
We kind of already
know those things.

00:07:34.930 --> 00:07:39.940
And from being around and going
on ride-alongs, but of the sort

00:07:39.940 --> 00:07:42.880
of conversation I'd start and
some of these conversations went

00:07:42.880 --> 00:07:48.470
on for years by the way, I would
simply say tell me about it.

00:07:48.470 --> 00:07:54.070
Keep it as open-ended as possible,
and there were veteran cops

00:07:54.070 --> 00:07:57.550
and retired cops and my wife came
along on some of these actually,

00:07:57.550 --> 00:08:01.080 position:56%
which was a big help because I think
that they opened up to her maybe

00:08:01.080 --> 00:08:04.670
in ways they wouldn't have opened
up to me, talking about cases

00:08:04.670 --> 00:08:07.230
that had happened 10, 20 years ago

00:08:07.230 --> 00:08:09.080
that I don't think
they ever talked about.

00:08:09.080 --> 00:08:10.380
And all of a sudden, you're looking

00:08:10.380 --> 00:08:16.760
at this very tough veteran homicide
cop, tears streaming down his face.

00:08:16.760 --> 00:08:18.470
&gt;&gt; Maureen Corrigan: I can
understand that from some

00:08:18.470 --> 00:08:21.710
of the stories that you had the
characters tell in the book.

00:08:21.710 --> 00:08:23.010
&gt;&gt; Don Winslow: Yeah.

00:08:23.010 --> 00:08:24.310
They're all true.

00:08:24.310 --> 00:08:25.610
&gt;&gt; Maureen Corrigan: Yeah, yeah.

00:08:25.610 --> 00:08:26.910
&gt;&gt; Maureen Corrigan: Did you
record those conversations?

00:08:26.910 --> 00:08:28.210
&gt;&gt; Don Winslow: No, no, no, no.

00:08:28.210 --> 00:08:29.510
Never. Don't record.

00:08:29.510 --> 00:08:30.810
Don't take notes.

00:08:30.810 --> 00:08:32.110
Nobody wants that.

00:08:32.110 --> 00:08:34.400
It makes you instantly unwelcome.

00:08:34.400 --> 00:08:35.950
And I'm not a journalist.

00:08:35.950 --> 00:08:39.600
I don't -- I try to make it as
realistic and as factually driven

00:08:39.600 --> 00:08:43.730
as I can, but I don't have the
responsibility that journalist has

00:08:43.730 --> 00:08:45.430
for absolute truth and accuracy.

00:08:45.430 --> 00:08:47.310
I'm still a fiction writer.

00:08:47.310 --> 00:08:51.060
But no, for me to have had a
microphone would not have worked

00:08:51.060 --> 00:08:55.510
in the situation at all or even to
be sitting there with the legal pad

00:08:55.510 --> 00:08:59.930
that I would have liked to
have had and taking things

00:08:59.930 --> 00:09:02.370
down would have inhibited
those conversations

00:09:02.370 --> 00:09:04.310
and inhibited those moments.

00:09:04.310 --> 00:09:07.570
I wouldn't have been the chair.

00:09:07.570 --> 00:09:08.870
Yeah.

00:09:08.870 --> 00:09:10.170
&gt;&gt; Maureen Corrigan:
Did any of them ask

00:09:10.170 --> 00:09:13.770
if they could read
what a draft of the --

00:09:13.770 --> 00:09:15.070
&gt;&gt; Don Winslow: No.

00:09:15.070 --> 00:09:20.010
No. I took that off the table.

00:09:20.010 --> 00:09:23.400
Listen, some of them have
really liked the book.

00:09:23.400 --> 00:09:26.190
Others have not.

00:09:26.190 --> 00:09:31.390
Some -- a little bit of both,
and that's what I expected,

00:09:31.390 --> 00:09:34.620
but for the most part, the reaction
has been very positive, but no.

00:09:34.620 --> 00:09:39.000
I would never let a subject read.

00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:42.050
Maybe for factual things,
